{"data_shared" : "some information from your browser may automatically be sent to the other company when you interact with buttons, tools, or content from other companies in Adobe Services and Software. reCAPTCHA Enterprise collects hardware and software information, and sends it to Google for purposes of providing, maintaining, and improving reCAPTCHA Enterprise and for general security purposes. Adobe shares contact and identifier information about you from your social networking account when you sign into some Adobe Services and Software using a social networking account. Adobe also shares information which you have made publicly available on your social networking account when you interact with Adobe’s social networking pages.", 

"data_collected": "Adobe may collect information about your use of features in Adobe Services and Software that link to other companies’ services. This includes content “liked” and address information in Google Maps. reCAPTCHA Enterprise collects hardware and software information. Adobe receives contact and identifier information about you from your social networking account when you sign into some Adobe Services and Software using a social networking account. Adobe collects information which you have made publicly available on your social networking account when you interact with Adobe’s social networking pages. Biometric identifiers or biometric information may be collected when you use certain features of Adobe Services and Software. When you visit an Adobe office, Adobe collects Identifiers and Contact information such as your name, company name, and email address; and Audio, electronic, visual, or similar information.", 

"security_practices" : "Adobe websites may implement Google reCAPTCHA Enterprise to help prevent spam and abuse. Adobe practices with respect to social networking pages and account sign-on services. Adobe follows the practice of deleting biometric identifiers or biometric information once you turn off the feature, unless otherwise specified in the Software or Services."}

{"data_shared" : "I may employ third-party companies and individuals due to the following reasons: To facilitate our Service; To provide the Service on our behalf; To perform Service-related services; or To assist us in analyzing how our Service is used. I want to inform users of this Service that these third parties have access to your Personal Information. The reason is to perform the tasks assigned to them on our behalf. However, they are obligated not to disclose or use the information for any other purpose.", 
"data_collected": "For a better experience, while using our Service, I may require you to provide us with certain personally identifiable information. The information that I request will be retained on your device and is not collected by me in any way. The app does use third party services that may collect information used to identify you. I want to inform you that whenever you use my Service, in a case of an error in the app I collect data and information (through third party products) on your phone called Log Data. This Log Data may include information such as your device Internet Protocol (“IP”) address, device name, operating system version, the configuration of the app when utilizing my Service, the time and date of your use of the Service, and other statistics.", 
"security_practices" : "I value your trust in providing us your Personal Information, thus we are striving to use commercially acceptable means of protecting it. But remember that no method of transmission over the internet, or method of electronic storage is 100% secure and reliable, and I cannot guarantee its absolute security."}
